Step 6: Run the Project

Build and start containers:

docker compose up --build


Access the app in your browser:

http://localhost:8080


NGINX will reverse proxy to Flask.

Flask connects to MySQL.

Data is persisted in a Docker volume.

Step 7: Verify Networking and Volumes

Check Docker containers:

docker ps


Inspect the network:

docker network ls
docker network inspect flask_mysql_nginx_app-network


Check volumes:

docker volume ls
docker volume inspect flask_mysql_nginx_db_data
